<exercise checkit-seed="0044" checkit-slug="M3" checkit-title="Invertible matrices">
  <statement>
    <p>Explain why the matrix <m>C= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
4 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 \\
2 &amp; -3 &amp; 6 &amp; 5 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 2 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 4 &amp; -8 &amp; -4
\end{array}\right] </m> is or is not invertible.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer><p><me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
4 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 \\
2 &amp; -3 &amp; 6 &amp; 5 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 2 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 4 &amp; -8 &amp; -4
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me></p><m>C</m> is not invertible.</answer>
</exercise>

